{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":557,"text":"In the space that used\nto house one transistor,"},{"time":4259,"text":"we can now fit one billion."},{"time":7636,"text":"That made it so that a computer\nthe size of an entire room"},{"time":11557,"text":"now fits in your pocket."},{"time":14170,"text":"You might say the future is small."}]},{"cues":[{"time":17611,"text":"As an engineer,"},{"time":18842,"text":"I'm inspired by this miniaturization\nrevolution in computers."},{"time":22851,"text":"As a physician,"},{"time":24223,"text":"I wonder whether we could use it\nto reduce the number of lives lost"},{"time":29970,"text":"due to one of the fastest-growing\ndiseases on Earth:"},{"time":34101,"text":"cancer."},{"time":35543,"text":"Now when I say that,"},{"time":36822,"text":"what most people hear me say\nis that we're working on curing cancer."},{"time":40624,"text":"And we are."},{"time":41911,"text":"But it turns out"},{"time":43086,"text":"that there's an incredible\nopportunity to save lives"},{"time":45911,"text":"through the early detection\nand prevention of cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49785,"text":"Worldwide, over two-thirds of deaths\ndue to cancer are fully preventable"},{"time":55188,"text":"using methods that we already\nhave in hand today."},{"time":58406,"text":"Things like vaccination, timely screening"},{"time":61329,"text":"and of course, stopping smoking."},{"time":64316,"text":"But even with the best tools\nand technologies that we have today,"},{"time":67933,"text":"some tumors can't be detected"},{"time":70020,"text":"until 10 years after\nthey've started growing,"},{"time":73714,"text":"when they are 50 million\ncancer cells strong."},{"time":78178,"text":"What if we had better technologies"},{"time":79881,"text":"to detect some of these more\ndeadly cancers sooner,"},{"time":83011,"text":"when they could be removed,"},{"time":84337,"text":"when they were just getting started?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":86562,"text":"Let me tell you about how\nminiaturization might get us there."},{"time":91140,"text":"This is a microscope in a typical lab"},{"time":93452,"text":"that a pathologist would use\nfor looking at a tissue specimen,"},{"time":97032,"text":"like a biopsy or a pap smear."},{"time":99927,"text":"This $7,000 microscope"},{"time":102019,"text":"would be used by somebody\nwith years of specialized training"},{"time":105299,"text":"to spot cancer cells."},{"time":108126,"text":"This is an image from a colleague\nof mine at Rice University,"},{"time":111196,"text":"Rebecca Richards-Kortum."},{"time":112798,"text":"What she and her team have done\nis miniaturize that whole microscope"},{"time":116649,"text":"into this $10 part,"},{"time":118648,"text":"and it fits on the end\nof an optical fiber."},{"time":121923,"text":"Now what that means is instead\nof taking a sample from a patient"},{"time":125581,"text":"and sending it to the microscope,"},{"time":127254,"text":"you can bring the microscope\nto the patient."},{"time":130260,"text":"And then, instead of requiring\na specialist to look at the images,"},{"time":134643,"text":"you can train the computer to score\nnormal versus cancerous cells."}]},{"cues":[{"time":140084,"text":"Now this is important,"},{"time":141278,"text":"because what they found\nworking in rural communities,"},{"time":144339,"text":"is that even when they have\na mobile screening van"},{"time":147602,"text":"that can go out into the community\nand perform exams"},{"time":150459,"text":"and collect samples"},{"time":151888,"text":"and send them to the central\nhospital for analysis,"},{"time":155128,"text":"that days later,"},{"time":156496,"text":"women get a call\nwith an abnormal test result"},{"time":159187,"text":"and they're asked to come in."},{"time":160828,"text":"Fully half of them don't turn up\nbecause they can't afford the trip."},{"time":165721,"text":"With the integrated microscope\nand computer analysis,"},{"time":169169,"text":"Rebecca and her colleagues\nhave been able to create a van"},{"time":172021,"text":"that has both a diagnostic setup\nand a treatment setup."},{"time":175831,"text":"And what that means\nis that they can do a diagnosis"},{"time":178569,"text":"and perform therapy on the spot,"},{"time":181280,"text":"so no one is lost to follow up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":183831,"text":"That's just one example of how\nminiaturization can save lives."},{"time":188148,"text":"Now as engineers,"},{"time":189325,"text":"we think of this\nas straight-up miniaturization."},{"time":192094,"text":"You took a big thing\nand you made it little."},{"time":194555,"text":"But what I told you before about computers"},{"time":196830,"text":"was that they transformed our lives"},{"time":199100,"text":"when they became small enough\nfor us to take them everywhere."},{"time":203785,"text":"So what is the transformational\nequivalent like that in medicine?"},{"time":208500,"text":"Well, what if you had a detector"},{"time":211660,"text":"that was so small that it could\ncirculate in your body,"},{"time":215946,"text":"find the tumor all by itself"},{"time":218383,"text":"and send a signal to the outside world?"},{"time":221079,"text":"It sounds a little bit\nlike science fiction."},{"time":223180,"text":"But actually, nanotechnology\nallows us to do just that."},{"time":227415,"text":"Nanotechnology allows us to shrink\nthe parts that make up the detector"},{"time":232320,"text":"from the width of a human hair,"},{"time":234181,"text":"which is 100 microns,"},{"time":235865,"text":"to a thousand times smaller,"},{"time":238444,"text":"which is 100 nanometers."},{"time":240370,"text":"And that has profound implications."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243583,"text":"It turns out that materials\nactually change their properties"},{"time":247250,"text":"at the nanoscale."},{"time":249279,"text":"You take a common material like gold,"},{"time":251801,"text":"and you grind it into dust,\ninto gold nanoparticles,"},{"time":255146,"text":"and it changes from looking\ngold to looking red."},{"time":259082,"text":"If you take a more exotic material\nlike cadmium selenide --"},{"time":262919,"text":"forms a big, black crystal --"},{"time":265117,"text":"if you make nanocrystals\nout of this material"},{"time":267742,"text":"and you put it in a liquid,"},{"time":269339,"text":"and you shine light on it,"},{"time":271187,"text":"they glow."},{"time":272377,"text":"And they glow blue, green,\nyellow, orange, red,"},{"time":278032,"text":"depending only on their size."},{"time":280887,"text":"It's wild! Can you imagine an object\nlike that in the macro world?"},{"time":284914,"text":"It would be like all the denim jeans\nin your closet are all made of cotton,"},{"time":291509,"text":"but they are different colors\ndepending only on their size."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296212,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":298982,"text":"So as a physician,"},{"time":300530,"text":"what's just as interesting to me"},{"time":302778,"text":"is that it's not just\nthe color of materials"},{"time":305102,"text":"that changes at the nanoscale;"},{"time":307057,"text":"the way they travel\nin your body also changes."},{"time":311137,"text":"And this is the kind of observation\nthat we're going to use"},{"time":313960,"text":"to make a better cancer detector."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316158,"text":"So let me show you what I mean."},{"time":318686,"text":"This is a blood vessel in the body."},{"time":320907,"text":"Surrounding the blood vessel is a tumor."},{"time":323683,"text":"We're going to inject nanoparticles\ninto the blood vessel"},{"time":326748,"text":"and watch how they travel\nfrom the bloodstream into the tumor."},{"time":331464,"text":"Now it turns out that the blood vessels\nof many tumors are leaky,"},{"time":335840,"text":"and so nanoparticles can leak out\nfrom the bloodstream into the tumor."},{"time":340628,"text":"Whether they leak out\ndepends on their size."},{"time":344129,"text":"So in this image,"},{"time":345303,"text":"the smaller, hundred-nanometer,\nblue nanoparticles are leaking out,"},{"time":349698,"text":"and the larger, 500-nanometer,\nred nanoparticles"},{"time":353118,"text":"are stuck in the bloodstream."},{"time":354919,"text":"So that means as an engineer,"},{"time":357046,"text":"depending on how big\nor small I make a material,"},{"time":361062,"text":"I can change where it goes in your body."}]},{"cues":[{"time":365249,"text":"In my lab, we recently made\na cancer nanodetector"},{"time":369915,"text":"that is so small that it could travel\ninto the body and look for tumors."},{"time":375477,"text":"We designed it to listen\nfor tumor invasion:"},{"time":379593,"text":"the orchestra of chemical signals\nthat tumors need to make to spread."},{"time":384932,"text":"For a tumor to break out\nof the tissue that it's born in,"},{"time":387858,"text":"it has to make chemicals called enzymes"},{"time":390598,"text":"to chew through\nthe scaffolding of tissues."},{"time":393763,"text":"We designed these nanoparticles\nto be activated by these enzymes."},{"time":399034,"text":"One enzyme can activate a thousand\nof these chemical reactions in an hour."},{"time":405462,"text":"Now in engineering, we call\nthat one-to-a-thousand ratio"},{"time":409044,"text":"a form of amplification,"},{"time":410633,"text":"and it makes something ultrasensitive."},{"time":412829,"text":"So we've made an ultrasensitive\ncancer detector."}]},{"cues":[{"time":417220,"text":"OK, but how do I get this activated\nsignal to the outside world,"},{"time":422144,"text":"where I can act on it?"},{"time":423906,"text":"For this, we're going to use\none more piece of nanoscale biology,"},{"time":427482,"text":"and that has to do with the kidney."},{"time":429659,"text":"The kidney is a filter."},{"time":431996,"text":"Its job is to filter out the blood\nand put waste into the urine."},{"time":437197,"text":"It turns out that what the kidney filters"},{"time":439883,"text":"is also dependent on size."},{"time":442901,"text":"So in this image, what you can see"},{"time":444865,"text":"is that everything smaller\nthan five nanometers"},{"time":447898,"text":"is going from the blood,\nthrough the kidney, into the urine,"},{"time":452027,"text":"and everything else\nthat's bigger is retained."},{"time":455176,"text":"OK, so if I make a 100-nanometer\ncancer detector,"},{"time":460147,"text":"I inject it in the bloodstream,"},{"time":462643,"text":"it can leak into the tumor\nwhere it's activated by tumor enzymes"},{"time":468097,"text":"to release a small signal"},{"time":470477,"text":"that is small enough to be\nfiltered out of the kidney"},{"time":473723,"text":"and put into the urine,"},{"time":475925,"text":"I have a signal in the outside world\nthat I can detect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":480588,"text":"OK, but there's one more problem."},{"time":482664,"text":"This is a tiny little signal,"},{"time":484434,"text":"so how do I detect it?"},{"time":486730,"text":"Well, the signal is just a molecule."},{"time":488989,"text":"They're molecules\nthat we designed as engineers."},{"time":491680,"text":"They're completely synthetic,\nand we can design them"},{"time":494882,"text":"so they are compatible\nwith our tool of choice."},{"time":498145,"text":"If we want to use a really\nsensitive, fancy instrument"},{"time":501611,"text":"called a mass spectrometer,"},{"time":503599,"text":"then we make a molecule\nwith a unique mass."},{"time":506671,"text":"Or maybe we want make something\nthat's more inexpensive and portable."},{"time":510394,"text":"Then we make molecules\nthat we can trap on paper,"},{"time":514201,"text":"like a pregnancy test."},{"time":515929,"text":"In fact, there's a whole\nworld of paper tests"},{"time":518579,"text":"that are becoming available\nin a field called paper diagnostics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523711,"text":"Alright, where are we going with this?"},{"time":526724,"text":"What I'm going to tell you next,"},{"time":528317,"text":"as a lifelong researcher,"},{"time":530167,"text":"represents a dream of mine."},{"time":532396,"text":"I can't say that's it's a promise;"},{"time":534513,"text":"it's a dream."},{"time":536029,"text":"But I think we all have to have dreams\nto keep us pushing forward,"},{"time":539640,"text":"even -- and maybe especially --\ncancer researchers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":543601,"text":"I'm going to tell you what I hope\nwill happen with my technology,"},{"time":547124,"text":"that my team and I will put\nour hearts and souls"},{"time":551239,"text":"into making a reality."},{"time":553289,"text":"OK, here goes."},{"time":555011,"text":"I dream that one day,"},{"time":558390,"text":"instead of going into\nan expensive screening facility"},{"time":561669,"text":"to get a colonoscopy,"},{"time":563198,"text":"or a mammogram,"},{"time":564545,"text":"or a pap smear,"},{"time":566585,"text":"that you could get a shot,"},{"time":568328,"text":"wait an hour,"},{"time":570012,"text":"and do a urine test on a paper strip."},{"time":573653,"text":"I imagine that this could even happen"},{"time":576484,"text":"without the need for steady electricity,"},{"time":579171,"text":"or a medical professional in the room."},{"time":581799,"text":"Maybe they could be far away"},{"time":583320,"text":"and connected only by the image\non a smartphone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":586854,"text":"Now I know this sounds like a dream,"},{"time":588613,"text":"but in the lab we already\nhave this working in mice,"},{"time":591756,"text":"where it works better\nthan existing methods"},{"time":593859,"text":"for the detection of lung,\ncolon and ovarian cancer."},{"time":598603,"text":"And I hope that what this means"},{"time":600861,"text":"is that one day we can\ndetect tumors in patients"},{"time":606061,"text":"sooner than 10 years\nafter they've started growing,"},{"time":609378,"text":"in all walks of life,"},{"time":611387,"text":"all around the globe,"},{"time":613260,"text":"and that this would lead\nto earlier treatments,"},{"time":616019,"text":"and that we could save more lives\nthan we can today,"},{"time":619641,"text":"with early detection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":621686,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622892,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}